02/05/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic said on Monday (1 May) that the independence referendum campaign is largely being conducted according to democratic standards, and that when violations occur, authorities are responding quickly. 
Vujanovic said he believes the results of the 21 May poll will be recognised by all parties within Serbia-Montenegro, as well as by the international community. 
(Tanjug, RTS - 01/05/06)
